SOS MULTI-CHAIN MESSAGING PROTOCOL

Final Architecture — 3 Channel System


---

SYSTEM OVERVIEW

SOS is a multi-chain, event-driven communication protocol.

It is designed as a neutral infrastructure where messages are recorded on blockchain networks and interpreted off-chain.

The system operates across three independent environments:

Ethereum (L1)

Ethereum Layer 2 networks

Solana


Each network represents a separate communication channel with its own cost structure and usage context.


---

CORE PRINCIPLE

SOS is not a traditional messaging app and not a financial token.

It is:

A public, append-only communication layer
where interactions are emitted as events
and meaning is resolved by users or applications


---

THREE CHANNEL MODEL

The system is intentionally divided into three independent channels.

There is:

no merging

no ranking

no weighting


Each channel exists as a separate communication lane.


---

Ethereum — Premium Channel

High cost per interaction.

Used for:

critical communication

high-value interactions

strong commitment signaling


This channel naturally filters noise due to economic cost.


---

L2 — Business Channel

Low cost and scalable.

Used for:

work communication

operational messaging

structured interactions


This channel balances efficiency and signal quality.


---

Solana — Personal / Mass Channel

Near-zero cost.

Used for:

family communication

social messaging

high-frequency interactions


This channel enables open access and mass usage.


---

CONTEXT SEPARATION

The system allows natural separation of life contexts:

Personal communication → Solana

Professional communication → L2

High-value communication → Ethereum


This removes the need for artificial filtering inside a single system.


---

USER IDENTITY MODEL

Identity is user-controlled.


---

Unified Identity (Unified Seed)

User links all wallets into one identity across chains.

Result:

consistent identity

shared history

cross-channel visibility



---

Separate Identities (Separate Seeds)

User maintains different identities per chain.

Result:

separation of personas

no automatic linkage

context isolation



---

MESSAGE MODEL

The protocol uses simple, abstract message types.

No meaning is enforced on-chain.


---

Mint

1 mint = 1 message

increases receiver’s interaction count

acts as a message on the receiver’s public wall



---

Trust

message type: trust

up to 3 participants

represents internal confirmation



---

Join

message type: acknowledgment

unlimited participants

represents external validation



---

EVENT-ONLY ARCHITECTURE

The protocol minimizes on-chain storage.

It does not store:

messages

agreements

relationships


It only records:

events

basic counters (balances)

identity anchors (seeds)



---

RESULT

The blockchain acts as:

A global, immutable event log
not a database of structured meaning


---

APPLICATION LAYER

All interpretation happens off-chain.

The application:

listens to all three chains

indexes events

displays them as separate channels



---

User Interface Concept

Users interact through clearly separated channels:

Family (Solana)

Work (L2)

Premium (Ethereum)


There is no automatic mixing between them.


---

COST AS A USER TOOL

Users choose the cost level of their communication:

low cost → Solana

medium cost → L2

high cost → Ethereum


Cost becomes a deliberate choice rather than a constraint.


---

RESILIENCE AND AVAILABILITY

Multi-chain architecture improves reliability.

If one network is:

congested

restricted

unavailable


Users can switch to another channel.


---

Example

Ethereum unavailable → use L2 or Solana

L2 congested → use Solana

Solana unavailable → use Ethereum



---

RESULT

Communication is not dependent on a single network.


---

SPAM AND SIGNAL DYNAMICS

Each channel has its own behavior:


---

Ethereum:

high cost

strong natural filtering



---

L2:

moderate cost

balanced filtering



---

Solana:

near-zero cost

requires application-level moderation



---

SYSTEM CLASSIFICATION

SOS is not:

a financial system

a payment network

a token economy

a ranking engine



---

SOS is:

A multi-channel communication protocol
with independent economic environments
and event-based interaction recording


---

ARCHITECTURE SUMMARY


---

Chain Layer:

Ethereum

L2

Solana



---

Protocol Layer:

Mint (message emission)

Trust (internal signal)

Join (external signal)



---

Identity Layer:

unified identity (optional)

separate identities (optional)



---

Application Layer:

indexing

display

filtering



---

KEY PROPERTIES

separation of communication contexts

user-controlled identity

cost-based interaction choice

resilience across networks

minimal on-chain storage

event-based architecture



---

FINAL STATEMENT

SOS is a multi-chain communication protocol that separates interactions by context, cost, and intent.

Users decide:

which network to use

how to structure identity

how much to spend per interaction


All communication is recorded as immutable events, while meaning and interpretation remain off-chain and user-defined.
